It is definitely not the Chicago White Sox.  It may be an industrial team; W could stand for "workers" or part of the name of the business, rather than "west".

I see there is an "X" by one of the players - is there anything written or stamped on the back of the holder?  If so, Ancestry.com or Findagrave would be a good starting place to track down a name.  What was the location of the place you purchased the image from - fair chance it stayed close to home all these years
